    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-16T04:11:01+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-16T04:11:01+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-15T18:41:01Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-15T18:41:01Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred over the Tasman Sea extends a ridge over the northeast of SA. A low pressure system will develop over the Bight on Monday then will remain slow-moving until later Thursday when it will move eastwards. An associated cold front will move across SA during Wednesday followed by a second front later Thursday. A high pressure ridge will move across from the west over the weekend.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds northwest to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures 21 to 27.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:00am to 2:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain east of Coober Pedy, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the early morning. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h before dawn. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the afternoon. Winds west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h tending west to southwesterly 25 to 40 km/h during the day then decreasing to 20 to 30 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Coober Pedy, slight chance elsewhere. Winds westerly 20 to 30 km/h turning southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h during the morning then decreasing to 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
